b"Thank you for believing in me for all these years, my music and my voice. The journey continues \xf0\x9f\x8d\xba *cheers* \n(That's a shandy) \xf0\x9f\x98\x89"
b'Being an artist is so fulfilling and terrifying at the same time. \nBut I love it. I know no other way.'
b'In saying all of this. I am excited to explore further into the feeling. To reflect on where I have been at my best and where I have not.'
b'Not sugar coated. But as it really is. Lyrics and melody change accordingly to feeling. As life changes. So do we.'
b'Music and singing are the only things I have ever known that make me feel what I feel transparently. Face to face with life.'
b"The feelings we want and need and the feelings we don't. They all matter. And to make other people feel what they need and want to feel."
b'One thing will never change. The reason why I make music and sing. To make myself feel free, to understand what my heart feels. All of it.'
b'My hair. My body. My fashion. My makeup. My nails. My life. My wants. My needs. My priorities. Have all changed a lot over past 10 years.'
b'So here I am. 27. 10 years into being signed where my journey as Jessie J began.'
b'The heartbeats who love my music, my voice, are respectful and understanding. Even if we have never met. I see you. You keep me going.'
b'You buy the music, come to my shows, sing along. Hold me up on a good day. Hold me up on a bad day.'
b'But my biggest thank you. Is to my heartbeats. My fans. You are with me through choice. And for that I will feel forever grateful.'
b"After 10 years I am so happy I still have that. I don't expect I don't presume. I work hard. I try my best to create from the inside out."
b"I didn't know what I was in for at 17 years old stepping into the world of music. I have days now where it feels unreal. A dream."
b'My label, my management, my publishers, my pr, my band, my team and all included on this ride. I am so thankful to work with special people.'
b"My journey so far has been so real. I've had huge success and songs out no one really noticed. Lol."
b"Takes time to build the 'perfect' team. I argue artist may never. And maybe that's a good thing. Because you never settle. You always push."
b'I have had both good and bad label experiences and both whilst having music out and known and also being completely unknown.'
b'It provides a platform to work alongside incredible creative people and a chance to build on your vision.'
b"Being signed doesn't create success overnight and it certainly doesn't give you all you ever wanted on a golden plate.."
